            <img class="rounded-circle" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAHd3dwAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" alt="Generic placeholder image" width="140" height="140">
            <h2>Build</h2>
            <p>Once the design is far enough to proceed and a plan is put in place I begin the majority of my work building the site. and testing it to get it ready for deployment. Hosting costs and registration fees are all paid up and a test server is contructed as well as a temporary landing page to seperate the private, under-contruction, side of the project from the pulic facing side.</p>
            <p><a class="btn btn-secondary" href="#Build" role="button">Build &raquo;</a></p>
          </div><!-- /.col-lg-4 -->
          <div class="col-md-3">
            <img class="rounded-circle" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAHd3dwAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" alt="Generic placeholder image" width="140" height="140">
            <h2>Deploy</h2>
            <p>When the website is ready for deployment it is uploaded to the application server and tested again to ensure that diffrences between the development, testign and production systems are all the same and the site functions as intended and expected. It doesn't end there..</p>
            <p><a class="btn btn-secondary" href="#Deploy" role="button">Deploy &raquo;</a></p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-3">
            <img class="rounded-circle" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAHd3dwAAACH5BAAAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" alt="Generic placeholder image" width="140" height="140">
            <h2>Support</h2>
            <p>The work isnt over once the site is goes "live". I'll still be there the entire time to tweek your SEO settings and drive traffic to your site and into your sales or contact funnels. Understanding your users and how they interact with your site is very important. And then there's maintainance</p>
            <p><a class="btn btn-secondary" href="#Support" role="button">Support &raquo;</a></p>
