        <!-- START THE FEATURETTES -->

        <hr class="featurette-divider">

        <div class="row featurette" id="Design">
          <div class="col-md-7">
            <h2 class="featurette-heading">Design&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="text-muted">more than just a look</span></h2>
            <p class="lead">This is not a website built from a template where you enter your specific information and the website is built on the fly by a bunch of automated functions. What I do is work with you on the site design and come up with a plan to build it. Each site is an application built from the ground up based on your design and budget. Your site data is housed in a private custom database, you can host your own discussion forums, have as many email lists as you need, surveys, or what ever else you desire.The possibilites are virtually unlimited.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-5">
            <img class="featurette-image img-fluid mx-auto" data-src="holder.min.js/500x500/auto" alt="Generic placeholder image">
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="featurette-divider">

        <div class="row featurette" id="Build">
          <div class="col-md-7 order-md-2">
            <h2 class="featurette-heading">Building The Site&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="text-muted">the longest phase of the process.</span></h2>
            <p class="lead">After the design is far enough along the development phase begins to take shape as I create the basics of the wireframed functional site. Once this is completed and the site functions as expected the layout, color and other style attributes are put into place and everything is tested to ensure it fucntions as intended and expected. Usually the site is deployed where the portions of the site that are not quite ready for public access are located in a private area until ready for actual live production use.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-5 order-md-1">
            <img class="featurette-image img-fluid mx-auto" data-src="holder.min.js/500x500/auto" alt="Generic placeholder image">
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="featurette-divider">

        <div class="row featurette" id="Deploy">
